In Salesforce 7, an Object is like a database table that stores related information in an organized way.
You can think of an object as a digital form or container used to keep records of a particular type of data.
For example:
A Customer object stores customer details
An Employee object stores employee information
A Product object stores product details
Each object contains:
Fields → individual pieces of information (like Name, Phone Number, Email)
Records → complete entries or rows of data
Example:
The Account Object in Salesforce is used to store information about companies or customers.
Example fields inside the Account Object:
Account Name
Phone Number
Address
Industry
